    .desc = Standard rules of the game EvacPod.

book-text-EvacPod-StandardRules = [bold][color=orange][head=2]EvacPod — Game Rules[/head][/bold]\n\n[bold]EvacPod[/bold] (an adaptation of the "Bunker" tabletop game) is a survival debate game.\n\n[bold]Story:[/bold]\nA terrible catastrophe has occurred on your space station. The only way to survive is to escape on the evacuation shuttle (evac pod). However, the number of seats inside is strictly limited to [color=red]half[/color] of the total number of players (rounded down).\n\n[bold]Goal:[/bold]\nConvince the other players that you deserve a seat in the evac pod to save your life and help rebuild the colony.\n\n[bold]Setup:[/bold]\n1. Unroll the EvacPod carpet.\n2. Each player draws one card of each category face down:\n   - [bold]Profession[/bold] (Profession)\n   - [bold]Biology[/bold] (Biology)\n   - [bold]Health[/bold] (Health)\n   - [bold]Hobby[/bold] (Hobby)\n   - [bold]Baggage[/bold] (Baggage)\n   - [bold]Fact[/bold] (Fact)\n   And 1-2 [bold]Special cards[/bold] (Special).\n\n[bold]Gameplay:[/bold]\nThe game is played in several rounds. In each round, every player must reveal one of their characteristics of their choice (except special cards, which are played according to their own rules) and explain in 30-60 seconds why they are useful for survival.\n\nAt the end of each round, an open discussion and vote take place. The player with the most votes is [color=red]expelled[/color] — they do not get a seat and are left behind on the dying station.\n\n[bold]Special Cards:[/bold]\nYou can play a special card at any time during your turn or according to the conditions written on the card. They can alter the vote, swap characteristics, or save you from expulsion.\n\n[bold]End of the Game:[/bold]\nThe game ends when the number of remaining players equals the number of seats in the pod. The survivors escape to safety!
